What you need to know:

President Cyril Ramaphosa’s Covid task team made their call to move the country into what he said was its new ‘near normal’, a state of crisis set to last months on current trends, based in part on a steady drop in known infections and deaths.Having had a severe 51 per cent collapse in economic activity due to the lockdown, there was also irresistible financial pressure to reopen, risks notwithstanding.